The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

                                        Archives
                                                                                                                                    NATION BRIEFS

    
	 Calcutta, Jan. 7 (PTI): A Mumbai-bound Indigo flight returned to Calcutta airport two hours after take-off today when a pregnant passenger took ill.
 Nayana Sheikh, 24, who was accompanied by husband Abdullah, told the crew she wasnt feeling well, an airport official said. They informed the pilot, who contacted the Calcutta air traffic control for a green signal to return. On reaching Calcutta, Abdullah took Nayana to hospital. The 7pm flight took off at 10pm.
  
	Chennai (PTI): The president of the Savera group of hotels, B.V.S. Reddy, has been arrested in connection with the collapse of a stage in his hotel during a New Year party which killed two persons.
  
	Akola (PTI): Two malnourished children have been admitted to a district hospital here. Collector Shrikar Pardeshi noticed the children while inaugurating the pulse polio programme on Sunday and ordered the health authorities to immediately take them to hospital.
  
	Srinagar (PTI): The Srinagar-Jammu national highway was thrown open for traffic on Monday after remaining closed for a day because of heavy snowfall on either side of the Jawahar tunnel. The snow has been cleared, a traffic department spokesman said.
  
	New Delhi (PTI): The Delhi consumer commission has asked General Motors to pay Rs 3 lakh as compensation to the widow of an advocate who was sold a defective car in 1996, drawing him into a legal battle till his death. G.L. Sanghi sent several letters to the auto-maker but the defects were not rectified. Sanghi filed a case in 1998 but after his death in January 2006, his family sold the car.
  
	 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): A retired army jawan has handed over a Quran, he had preserved for 36 years to local clerics. Shyam Singh had found the holy book in Pakistan during the 1971 war. He was honoured by the clerics for his gesture.
                                                           
